main event: An airline pilot reported several light colored objects traveling in a V-formation near LaCrosse, Wisconsin on April 14, 1952.
interesting points: The objects were observed at high speeds and exhibited straight and level maneuvers,The sighting was made during the day,The length of observation was several minutes,Even though the airline pilot reported this, there was no follow-up investigation,The incident was documented in Project Blue Book, indicating official interest.
sighted object: several light colored objects in V-formation
